result.execSummary:
The defendant Kenneth Frank Trapp was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant, Kenneth Frank Trapp appeared with Attorney R Michael Waterman.  Attorney Frost appeared for the State.  Also has 14 CF 60.  1:05 pm Court calls cases and recites appearances.  State recites plea - amended info was filed today - recites agreement.  Atty Waterman agreed with State's stmt.  Court doesn't normally accept a no contest plea on a felony battery.  Atty Waterman makes further stmt.  Court with that he will accept a NC plea.  Court questions the defendant re: plea questionnaire.  14 CF 50 motion is granted to reflect Misd. bail jumping.  Plea of nc entered by defendant.  Court accepts pleas and finds defendant guilty.  State makes stmt re: sentencing.  Court questions the state.  Atty Waterman makes stmt re: sentencing.  Defendant addressed the Court.

COURT:  
14 CF 30 - Count 1 Accepts DGPA and defers entry of judgment on the felony charge battery

counts 2 and 3 - and 14 CF 50 - sentence w/held probation 3 yrs - concurrent to each other - 30 days conditional jail forthwith w/o huber - costs count 2 and 4 14 CF 50 - $443.00 dna surcharge as to OWI - $1179.00 - IID - 12 mo revocation IID 12 months as well - AODA - successfully complete domestic abuse class and cognative thinking class - maintain sobriety - random testing by DOC - no contact with Susan Slater or her residence or her employment - written apology to be directed to DOC and Victim Witness Office of the DA - terms of DGPA are also to be included with probation - restitution to be determined w/i statutory time frame.  Remanded to WCSO
